fields.title: Description
fields.value: Zhenya Gloomy is found, we need to go get some vodka for further conversation.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: He can't come up himself? He's getting lazy, the old devil. But come on, get your drink and roll away from the bar. You're spreading bacilli here.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Zhenya told me to go and talk to Bubna, wondering what he is like

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Where should I look for this Fort

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Some bar called Borzhch has one percent more customers than ShTI. Bubna sent me to that bar to find out why people go there.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: We need to get out of here quickly to Bubna!

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Well, that's it, I was more afraid. As long as they don't get caught now, the rest doesn't matter. Now we have to switch the vodka in the bar "Borzhch"

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Put the burnt vodka in the warehouse Borzhch

fields.title: Name
fields.value: Give the vodka to the Storekeeper

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Need to talk to the middleman of Bubna aka Silken, thanks for the tag, you old cunt!

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Phew... I hope he didn't figure out it was me. The main thing now is that the warehouse guard doesn't suspect anything.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: I have to find a hole in the wall through which I can get into the military commissary's territory

fields.title: Name
fields.value: In the jaws of the lion

fields.title: Description
fields.value: The first stash will be near the gas station tanker

fields.title: Description
fields.value: There will be a second stash on the roof of the building next to the gas station

fields.title: Description
fields.value: The third stash is behind a large building to the left of the road, on the way to Bubna, there is also an eternal flame

fields.title: Success Description
fields.value: What happened to them... Korenastiy in the "Messages" app - My man reported everything, well done butcher, you can go to Zhenka Gloomy, count me in for remembering you.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Helped to Korenastiy too, now back to Zheka

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Ch-4 seems to be over now, so it's time to get to the real Zone. I have to go to the swamps. And already there, at the base, to talk to the local leader of the stalkers - Gurvinok. Label stalker base is already in my PDA, I must go to Genok at the gas station, he then will take the Zone.

fields.title: Name
fields.value: To the Gofer for the load

fields.title: Description
fields.value: I took on an errand, I have to moan on the mark, talk to my kent, then pick up his cargo and deliver it to Vasiliy.

fields.title: Name
fields.value: Take a load to the Gloomy

fields.title: Description
fields.value: A new task is much more difficult than the previous one: I need to disrupt the deal between the stalkers and the leftist bandits. It will take place in some basement.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I dunno. It just isn't my thing. Here, have a banana.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: BRAAAII... Oh, it's you again. Hi!

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Well you have survivin' to do. I won't keep you.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Alright man, first go through obstacles, then talk to man on other side

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Good job, now try to test weapon and equipment

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You can add attachments to weapon on modification table

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Available attachments are displaying in weapon description

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Your equipment have base stats, you can check all info in item description

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: When you are ready, talk to man next to radiation alert

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: There are 4 types of contamination, which have 3 stages of danger

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Biological usually appears near toxic places such as kissel pools

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Thermal contamination appears only near thermal anomalies

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Psy contamination located on high places and map borders

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Now get through them with appropriate suits

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: When you enter zone, you will find a lot of anomalies

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Mostly of them are not so dangerous and can drop various artefacts

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Avoid blackhole anomalies, they will kill you instantly

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: All anomalies, artefacts and their description you can find in guides section of website

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Artefacts are drops near anomalies after emission release

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: All other useful information you will find on website

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: There you can also use auction and edit your character

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: This is alpha version of the game

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Head to the Driver, he will take you to the swamps

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I want to go to the zone

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I won't drive for free, this will cost you 100 000

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: This ride will be very risky, there are a lot of military forces near the border

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You can get there on foot

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Come here, when you will get money

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I can give you 10% discount no more

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I want to join your faction

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: We got enough pals, go away

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Maybe I can do something for you?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Recently one bastard killed our courier with very significant supplies

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: If you find and bring these supplies to me, I will think about your decision

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Alright, where should I search them?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You want me to be your flunky?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Ok, maybe it was too bold

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: He was going from machine yard, I think you will find them somewhere here

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I will pay enough for this

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Not good, we got big losses recently

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Do you want to join us?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: One bastard killed our courier with supplies, if you find them, I will know that you are not burden

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: This location is controlled by stalker and bandit factions

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I reccomend you to talk to their leaders first

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: It is located near railway on North-West

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: There is no big difference between them, except their location

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: In front of you sits a certain man with a gloomy look and drinks vodka.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: It's personal. What are you doing here, by the way? I'm usually the only one here on the second floor.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Don't break, you're not a girl! Do you want some vodka?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Why not? By the way, my name is ...

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value:
It's okay. My name is Zheka, my nickname is "Gloomy". A lot of people here know me. *Shouting* Bartender, vodka.
Bartender: Get your ass up and get it.
Zheka: I ain't got no fucking energy, go get some vodka from the bar, you're on your feet now anyway.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Well, did you bring the hot water?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Yes, I did! What are we drinking?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value:
Of course we do. To getting to know you! What are you doing here, by the way? I'm, like, the only regular customer at this eatery. 
Bartender: Call my cafe a eatery again, you'll be eating vodka on the bench behind the station with Semenych.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Ah, what to hide - I want to get into the Zone, but do not know how.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value:
Bartender: *Laughs* Until the first bullet? And then with a cry of "Mom!" back? Not my problem, though. 
Zheka: you're in the right place, man. I'm just ethics, but not for free. you go to the checkpoint, on the Ch-4 meet me. If they ask who you're from, tell them you're from me.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Young man, show me your pass or leave.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Buddy don't worry I'm from Zheka from the station

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Well, brother, were you not searched there? Just kidding. Hey, you need to make some useful acquaintances with some people with a capital letter for the first time. One is Bubna and the other is Korenastiy. You go to Bubna now, let's start with him. Get to know him, talk to him, help him with his business. You know what I mean.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Calmer I am a man of Zhenya Gloomy

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Zhenka? Gloomy? We'll check it out. You'll lose your legs and arms if you lie.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I came from Zheka to meet you

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: From Zheka? You're not fucking around? Look, I don't keep liars alive for long.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: What are you afraid of? Do I look like a liar?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Yeah, that's exactly what it looks like. All right, you're just in time. I need a little help here. If you're lying about being from Zheka, that'll count for something.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: No, that's not good enough, I thought we'd just talk, that's all.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: It's not that easy, but don't be afraid either, it's easy. Just take a walk, that's all. Anyway, straight to the point. You have to go to a local bar called "Borzhch", It's not a great bar, ours is cooler, but still a certain percentage of customers go there. Find out why they like it so much and lure customers to us.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Maybe they don't have any money? I'll go find out.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: *A drunken man is sitting in front of you, muttering something under his breath*

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Hey man, are you all right?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Yee-haw, eek! What do you want?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Listen, why are you sitting in such a hole? Go to ShTI instead.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Really? I don't know, I spent the best years of my life in that bar... I'll go see that ShTI sometime, Eek! If they'll let me in.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: They'll let you in, don't worry

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: So, how's it going? Did you get the customers?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Naturally, there was just one problem.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Which one, if it's not a secret?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: The bartender threatened me with a double-barrelled gun.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Is it all so sad? Well, we'll ask him again. Now there's a more difficult task waiting for you. You have to swap out a box of good vodka from the bandits for burnt vodka. Most of my clients go crazy for "Absolut Crystal" vodka. I was recently told that the bandos at the "Anchor" Bar had received a shipment of four or five boxes. If you steal it quietly and leave, no one will notice. We get the money and the prestige, but they get the fingers and the problems. By the way, swap out the plain vodka for the bar "Borzhch" just as a preventive measure, so they don't fuck with us.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Oh, shit, if they catch me, I'll be fucked.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Did you come here to win my favor or to whine? Probably the former. So don't whine, go to work. You can get some vodka at the warehouse outside the bar.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Whoa! It's all there. Here, take a couple of blood money for household expenses. And that's the last assignment for you.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Uh-oh! What am I, a nigger, to do this kind of work!

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Nigger not nigger, I told you about the whining. If you keep whining, you'll go to the woods and you won't see any Zone. The last task for you is to pick up the flash card from the mediator in one hut, and then take it to me, the coordinates have already forwarded to you. If anything, the call sign of the mediator - "Silken". *laughs*

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You have a "closet" of considerable size in front of you - clearly you should not swear with such a closet.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Silken? I'm from Bubna, for the Flash card.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: How did you call me? Did you want to get punched in the jaw, or haven't you picked your teeth up on the floor in a long time? So go ahead and call me Silken again!

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Bubna introduced you to me, I had nothing to do with it.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: There's your fucking flash on the windowsill. Oh, shit, rat wounds hurt so much. Get the fuck out of here!

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Well, did you get the flash card?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Place it here then and blow back now to Zhenya

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Bubna was a pain in the ass: find the flash drive, steal the vodka...

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You're funny, all right. Now I need you to go to Korenastiy. You be careful there, this guy is a bandit bumpkin. If Bubna asked you to mess with bandits, you better pray they don't recognize you. There's no other way out.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Do you want me dead too?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: No, I'll make money off you, that's why I need you alive. Now come on, let's saddle up!

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: *Next to you sitting a formidable-looking man, you need to be careful how you talk to him*

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: That's the one, why did you come here?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I'm from Zheka, getting to know the local authorities.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: It's nice to hear such words in my address. I haven't heard such words in a long time, although in fact I have. So what exactly do you need?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I need to be remembered for you.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Remembered? You do a couple of tasks for me, and we're even.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: How about a couple of catchphrases?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Bold? I like that, you'll go far. And in order for me to remember you, you have to make a few things for me. This is a mandatory aspect.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: What if a great vodka is added to the winged phrases?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Another talk! A couple of shots to get acquainted. Or a couple of bottles... In short, bring five bottles of vodka and a snack.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: At least you didn't get your vodka at the dump?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You're insulting, the best vodka around!

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Well, here's to getting to know each other *drinks a shot of vodka* Speaking of vodka. Some faggot stole our most kosher vodka. That's your first assignment. Ask the people at the warehouse if they've seen any suspicious faces.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: *drink a shot* Some bum probably stole it when he was hungry.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Bums wouldn't swap her out for a finger. Come on, just look for the immortal Fraerok.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: *Typical person of such job sitting in front of you*

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Hey, have you seen anyone suspicious around here?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: What do you need it for?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Crystal vodka was stolen from the warehouse. I'm looking for an asshole, have you seen it or not?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I saw it, Warden, I saw it. A bum was hanging around, looked a bit like you, but where are your shackles and your pants, since you're a detective?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You can get punched in the teeth for comparing me to a hobo, and no shackles, I'm not cop.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: So you are yours? That's good, that's respect. I ain't seen nobody here but a bum with a bag. I'll tell you, that scumbag swiped some vodka from the warehouse. If anything, he usually hangs around the construction site or the garages.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Sound asleep, not forgetting to snore, to the whole neighborhood

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Wake up! The warehouse was robbed! Did you see that?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Huh? What? Why the fuck did you wake me up?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I'm telling you, the warehouse was robbed! Did you see anyone suspicious?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Of course! He's talking to me right now.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Don't you think I'm serious? Don't you respect me? I didn't see it, but I heard something rustling in the bushes in my sleep, and then I heard a fence crunching, I thought it might be rats, I can't tell you anything else, get lost.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You're fast. How are you doing?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I was right, there was a bum hanging around the warehouse

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Well, then we should draw and quarter him. I'll have my men find him and send him to his death. You have a more responsible task now. I would even say suicidal.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: We're all going to die someday... There's nothing complicated there, if you're careful. Just sneak into the military office for a couple of documents. The main thing is to act quietly, without being seen by the guards. There's a hole in the fence, next to the military commissary, and I don't know how the soldiers haven't found it yet. In general, to the left of the main entrance there are bushes, there is a hole. Dive into it and that's it! You're already in closed territory. Further, skips behind the boxes and shelters bypass patrols and guards, climb to the second floor on the tube, find the office of the commissar, etc. ... It's easy! If anything, it's in the right wing on the third floor.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Yeah easy, I hope you'll pay a lot of money for that?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You're insulting. I'll pay you in full. By the way, find a gun of some kind, you'll need it.

fields.title: Title
fields.value: Ch-4/In the jaws of the lion

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Looking through a desk drawer. You find the treasured documents marked "Secret"

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You find someone's PB and ammunition in the drawers ofthe table.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Oh, alive! Did you find the documents?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Of course I did, I don't see any other way.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: So you found the gun. This is not the end of your work, now we need to distribute the rolls in places.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Good thing this job is safer than prying into the military

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Here's your ammunition. We never found that thief. That's why we need a genocide. Go to the garages and take out some garbage, nobody needs them anyway.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Give me ammo I'm blood thirsty

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: That's how you should answer, not roll your snot all over your fist.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: So, did you meet him? And how? Well, never mind. Now in the building happened, shots, shouting, etc... You'll have a choice there: Stalkers or Bandits. I won't keep you long, go on.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: In front of you the elevator control panel

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: The Flash Card is in front of you. Apparently, one of the factions didn't have time to pick it up, the other faction swooped in. What do you choose?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Look, we've already shot too much here. The peacekeepers, though they're lazy bitches, are interested! If you're a Stalker, we'll show you all the possibilities of the zone! And not a single good stalker soul will die at the hands of those scumbags again. You know what they do, don't you, with the likes of you or me? And there's no less interesting. Stalker life waiting for you. Don't hesitate, take the flash drive and bring it to Bubna!

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Parya, we're making a lot of noise here, let's think about it. The soldiers can come at any moment. If you stick with the Bandits, you'll be the king of your life. You'll have lots of money, pussies and adrenaline. We'll help you become a real man, but only in the beginning, because real men don't need other people's help. So don't think, grab a flash drive and drag it to Korenastiy, he'll thank you in full, come on man, make your choice, and with these suckers, we'll deal with it somehow.
